  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you have forgotten your User ID and password for your HDFC Forex card, you can follow these steps to retrieve or reset them:\n\n### For User ID Recovery:\n1. **Visit the HDFC Bank Website:** Go to the official HDFC Bank website.\n2. **Forex Services Section:** Navigate to the Forex card section or the 'Customer Care' section.\n3. **User ID Retrieval:** Look for the option to recover your User ID. You may need to provide information such as your registered mobile number or email address to verify your identity.\n\n### For Password Reset:\n1. **Login Page:** Go to the login page for HDFC Bank's Forex services.\n2. **Forgot Password Option:** Click on the 'Forgot Password' link.\n3. **Verification Process:** Follow the on-screen instructions. You will likely need to enter your User ID and other details to verify your identity.\n4. **Receive Reset Link:** You may receive an email or SMS with a link to reset your password.\n\n### Additional Help:\n- **Customer Support:** If you are unable to recover your User ID or reset your password online, contact HDFC Bank's customer service for assistance. You can call their helpline or visit your nearest HDFC Bank branch.\n- **Documentation:** Be prepared to provide identification or other relevant details to verify your identity.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Ensure that you keep your credentials secure and avoid sharing them with anyone.\n- Update your contact information with HDFC Bank to receive notifications and alerts.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to regain access to your Forex card account.",
